The Detection Rules Pipeline Bot delivers real-time notifications for the automated YARA detection rule lifecycle managed through our internal GitLab instance.

This bot provides visibility into pipeline events that would otherwise require manually checking GitLab, including community rule Merge Request submissions and approvals, validation pass/fail results, and successful rule publish events to the production detection rules repository.

Our GitLab instance operates in an isolated network enclave without email notification capability, making this Slack integration the primary mechanism for keeping the team informed of pipeline activity.

Notifications cover:
- Merge Request events — when community rules are submitted, updated, or merged
- Pipeline status — when the weekly rule fetch and publish pipeline succeeds or fails
- Validation results — when rules fail to compile or duplicate names are detected
- Publish confirmations — when updated rules are successfully pushed to the production repository

This bot is read-only and posts notifications only. It does not respond to messages or commands.
